ss=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(7/26/01 6:53:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Twinking a cleric</span><hr size=1> I've decided to twink out alittle baby cleric so I have something to do when I can't get groups with my main or get bored doing solb/velks/ect.  I am curious what people around here think I should do for EQ, if I should go wis early on or let that ride due to the low output of mana to wisdom at low levels.  Advice on cheap to midrange items would also be appreciated. (Character is a High Elf but may just remake as a DE or Halfling... the dwarf quest helm is just too ugly...)<br>
<br>
*edit opps forgot to mention my main is a 50 warrior* <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uvalnirlanys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valnir Lanys</A> at: 7/26/01 8:56:32 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uulme.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ulme</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(7/26/01 7:13:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Twinking a cleric</span><hr size=1> Adamantite Epolets, good ac, 7 wis is good for shoulders and common drop from a fairly simple mob<br>
<br>
Gatorscale leggings are nice...<br>
<br>
Spirit tome in Kaesora is fairly easy to get, I at least think that one was cleric usable, got it for my druid recently.<br>
<br>
Buy 2x 6 wis rings perhaps<br>
<br>
Can't come up with much more from the top of my head :) Hope it helps a tiny bit at least <p><font color="pink"><B><I>Varlek Khailderian, level 52 Dwarven Vicar of Dark Whispers</I></B></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukiitykatt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KiityKatt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(7/26/01 8:42:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Twinking a cleric</span><hr size=1> I am still working on twinking my cleric and she is level 24 and also a highelf. As of yesterday her wisdom is 200 and I still have to get good leg and feet items. Would like to get rid of what she has on her head and a a tiara with hp and mana on it.  <br>
The hardest part of  twinking HIE cleric is they have such low strength so I would appreciate any advice as to what to get to up the ac and keep weight down.<br>
<br>
Kiity Katt<br>
40 necromancer<br>
<br>
Chrysty<br>
24 cleric <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulaellanna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laellanna</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(7/26/01 9:34:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Twinking a cleric</span><hr size=1> It depends on how much pp you have... I think this is what I did personally:<br>
<br>
Head - Savant's Cap (3wis, 3ac).. probably 30pp<br>
Neck - Goblin Soul Caller (5wis) .... ~300pp<br>
Face - Plat. Ruby Veil (7wis/str)... ~500pp<br>
Wrist, Legs, Feet, Hands, Chest ... cleric quest items ~2.5kpp<br>
Shoulder - Adamantite Epolets (9? wis)... ~200pp<br>
Waist - Thick Leather Apron (good for AC)... 20pp<br>
Ears - Forest Loops... 300pp each<br>
Fingers - +6wis rings... ~300pp each<br>
Back - Cloak of the Ice Bear (for AC)... ~100pp<br>
Primary - Yak Club (9dmg/25dly)... ~1.5kpp<br>
Shield - CGS (9wis)... ~600?pp<br>
<br>
I twinked a heck of a long time ago, so the prices were  a bit higher back then.  But with this setup, the first few levels are much easier.  (Sorry to those who dislike twinking.. but this subject IS about that very topic).<br>
<br>
Laellanna - Virtuoso<br>
Daena - High Priestess<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uuilarblakheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Uilar Blakheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(7/26/01 10:34:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Twinking a cleric</span><hr size=1> Yes it does depend on how much pp you have, but it also depends on what your main is.  I have a DE necro, and was able to farm most of the items I needed to twink my cleric.  This is my cleric's set up from day 1 and he is still using all the items.  I have myself a nice mixture of STR, WIS, and AC.  Yes, clerics need STR.  Hard to carry around pp and items to sell with no str.<br>
<br>
Head - Runed Circlet<br>
Neck - Goblin Soul Caller<br>
Face - Velium Ruby Veil<br>
Wrist - Bracers of the Reverent<br>
Arms - Donal's Vambraces<br>
Legs - Ry Gorr Leggings<br>
Feet - Dwarven Work Boots<br>
Hands - Guantlets of the Black<br>
Chest - Ry Gorr Battlemail<br>
Waist - Belt of the Cenobyte<br>
Ears - Forest Loop, Ivandyr's Hoop (still has all charges)<br>
Fingers - +6wis rings<br>
Back - Kunzar Cloak<br>
Primary - Dark Ember<br>
Secondary - CGS<br>
Range - Wisdom Deity<br>
<br>
Cleric's Wisdom is 200, AC is 698, STR is 91 at lvl 40. <br>
 <br>
If you can get it, I would advise getting a Clay Guardian Shield at early lvls since you will be tanking some, and 9 wis won't help you that much.  Can also replace the wisdom rings with moonstone rings that drop from Frenzied Ghoul in L Guk.  The rings are +3 str, +30m.  The plus 60m you will receive more than make up for the loss of 12 wis in the beginning, and the +6str will help with your attack.<br>
<br>
Uilar, 53 Heretic<br>
Stryyke, 49 ranger<br>
Uilaar, 40 cleric <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubettyaspoon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BettyASpoon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(7/26/01 1:41:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Twinking a cleric</span><hr size=1> Bah,  These posts are soooo depressing to people who have clerics as their mains.  46 cleric, and my wis is like 161 ('course being a DE doesn't help).  And I'm still wearing a 6AC Cloak hehe.<br>
