</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ufelishannasecretlight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Felishanna Secretlight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(7/26/01 4:32:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Twinking a cleric</span><hr size=1> OOC.<br>
Dont feel bad Moerne. Feli was wearing a banded cloak (that she blacksmithed herself, and proud of it she was too) until her high 40s. Twinks comparing etchings is all fine and good, but those with soul do it the 'hard' way <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  .<br>
<br>
Btw, all this concentration on WIS at low level is not clever. At say level 15, each point of WIS only gives 3 mana points, so that +6wis ring is only +18mana .... in general, you are far better off with +Mana, +HP and +AC items (assuming like most players are are money limited). WIS only becomes important to get high when you get into the 40s or so.<br>
<br>
Feli's unbuffed WIS with her default gear was only 185 at level 60 until about 3 weeks ago. Only as a result of two new things she acquired recently has she made 200 at last. So don't let the twinks and farmers make you bitter. 161 WIS at your level is fine, it's about what my cleric had at the time. Good skill matters far more than having no skill and more WIS. Play your own game and have fun. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <p>------------------------------<BR>
Felishanna Secretlight<BR>
High Priestess of Tunare<BR>
Heroes of the Old Lands<BR>
Lanys T'Vyl.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uvalnirlanys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valnir Lanys</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(7/26/01 8:31:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Twinking a cleric</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the info on wisdom gear, thats what I really wanted to know and thats what I had thought.  Any one have any info on juggling all that heavy plate with a base str of 70 or might I be better off going with a stronger race than the feeble HIE. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udonord.showPublicProfile?language=EN>donord</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(7/26/01 10:07:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Twinking a cleric</span><hr size=1> i tend to agree with felish.  until level 50 10 mana &gt; 1 point of wisdom.  and hp is incredibly important as you are learning how to handle your agro in a grouped encounter.  particularly when you are still not grouping with enchanters.<br>
<br>
and really there is no real reason to max wis/mana till you are a raiding cleric.  most of your groups will be very mana un intensive.  it wasn't until i started raiding full time that i concerned myself with my overall mana pool because of the length of encounters with 100khp mobs and the damage that those mobs crank out / second.<br>
<br>
i was at 180 some wis till around 58 when i started completing velious armor quests which have mana and wis on every piece and run at a cool 249 wis (talk about overkill) now. <p>- <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=26259">Donord</a> <br>
High Priest of Visions</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukayshasoulsinger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaysha Soulsinger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(7/27/01 1:04:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Twinking a cleric</span><hr size=1> I remember when I was around lvl 30 or so, and worried that my Wisdom was around 150 or so. From many Castersrealm profiles it was obvious that a lot of Clerics had higher wisdom than me. Personally, I wondered how I ever was to get anywhere near 200 Wisdom.<br>
<br>
Right now, at lvl 50, I have 206 Wisdom, with gear equiped. I used to have 207 even, but changed a little to my outfit recently (added a +mana item to it). Wacky, especially since I have been around 200 ever since my low 40's.<br>
<br>
My Cleric is my first character ever and still my main, and therefore untwinked. I'll try and give a breakdown of the gear I currently have:<br>
<br>
- Ivandyr's Hoop (Wis+6)<br>
- Goblin Soul Caller (Wis+5)<br>
- Velium Ruby Veil (Wis+8 ) <br>
- Runed Circlet (Wis+4)<br>
- Forest Loop (Wis+3)<br>
- Velium Jasper Ring (Wis+7)<br>
- Bracer of the Reverent (Wis+5)<br>
- Imbued Field Plate Vambraces (Wis+4)<br>
- Imbued Field Breastplate (Wis+4)<br>
- Bracer of the Reverent (Wis+5)<br>
- Velium Jasper Ring (Wis+7)<br>
- Adamantite Epaulets (Wis+7)<br>
- Cloak of the Ry'Gorr Oracles (Wis+2)<br>
- Imbued Field Plate Greaves (Wis+4)<br>
- Gauntlets of the Black (Wis+3)<br>
- Girdle of the Diligent (Wis+5)<br>
- Crystal Lined Slippers (Wis+3)<br>
- Velium Etched Stone Mace (Wis+3)<br>
- Book of Obulus (Wis+8 ) <br>
- Seal of Thoridain (Wis+3)<br>
<br>
This adds up to 96 Wisdom total. My base wisdom is 110, bringing me to 206.<br>
<br>
All this gear I have worked for. Either by buying it from other players with the money I made, through questing / camping the correct MoBs, or made them myself (the Imbued stuff). Nothing twinked. Admitted, the Girdle was a gift from a parting Cleric, but it replaced my Crystalline Belt (Wis+3).<br>
<br>
I'm currently looking into getting more resist gear, and mana gear, as a result <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p><br><A Href="http://www.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=30878"><IMG
SRC="http://members.rott.chello.nl/ldirks/www/KayshaSoulsinger.jpg"></a><BR>
Cleric in the 50th Circle of Erollisi Marr <BR>
<i>The road to Heaven is paved with stones from Hell</i></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukayshasoulsinger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaysha Soulsinger</A> at: 7/27/01 1:05:13 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucalbegath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Calbegath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(7/27/01 10:04:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Twinking a cleric</span><hr size=1> If yer starting a twink cleric from scratch, it's prolly useful ta keep in mind that a cleric makes a very solid tank fer the first 15 levels or so.  Rather than focusing on +wis gear, go fer AC:  banded at the least, fine plate if ye can afford.  (Bronze may not be the best option due ta weight.)  Some of the good +wis items are cheap and ye'll get a lot of use of them, like adamantite shoulders, but given the choice ye'll want AC over +wis early on.<br>
<br>
At low levels HP and mana gear are vital.  It's me opinion that the absolute cleric twink weapon of choice (and really this goes fer all casters) is the staff of the observers (12/35 +5wis +5int +30mana).   Nice stats, hits hard fer level, very cheap (they go as low as 100pp).  Dark ember and CGS combo is good if price is no object, but nothing kills bears like a 2hb. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Other cheap goodies include gold jade bracelets (3ac +15hp/mana), polished bone hoops (+10 mana), plat fire opal rings (5ac +55hp) or jade (4ac +20hp/mana); go velium if money is no object.<br>
<br>
Oh, and while yer twinked ta the gills, be sure ta learn what spells ye have and how they work; ye'll need those skills later, obviously, and with good gear the risk of screwing up is a lot lower. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <p>Cheers,<br>
<br>
<img src="http://members.aol.com/deepgreyocean/calb.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulaellanna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laellanna</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(7/27/01 11:28:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Twinking a cleric</span><hr size=1> If it makes you feel any better Feli and Betty, my cleric had her barbed arms until level 60, and also her cleric quest BP until she maxed out 60 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
And you're right, in the end you really have to learn your spells, agro management, and mana efficiency.  Heck, with that crappy gear, my cleric still managed to go and do a one group Jugg raid and get all the way to the bridge before Trak's lair.<br>
